    <h1>Mini Biography: Mahatma Gandhi ji</h1>
    <p>Mahatma Gandhi(1869-1948) was one of the greatest leaders of India's freedom struggle.</p>

    <h2>Early Life</h2>
    <p>He was born in Porbandar, Gujarat on 2 oct 1869. he completed his early schooling in Rajkot. He was a honest and
        shy child. </p>
    <p><small>Note: This Biography is only a example. You may replace Mahatma Gandhi with any personality you admire.</small></p>

    <h2>Important Achievement</h2>
    <p>He led <strong>India's freedom movement through truth(satyaghraha) and non-violence(Ahimsa)</strong>.</p>
    <p>He inspired <em>millions of people</em> to fight peacefully for India's independence.</p>
    <p>One value that made him special was his commitment to <mark>truth, non-violence and simplicity</mark>.</p>

    <h2>Correction Corner</h2>
    <p><s>Gandhi was not only a freedom fighter.</s> He was also a lawyer, social reformer, and leader.</p>

    <h2>Interesting Examples</h2>
    <p>Science reminds us of formulas like H<sub>2</sub>O and ideas like 10<sup>2</sup>.</p>
    <p>He also encouraged students to become the 1<sup>st</sup> version of themselves, not a copy of someone else.</p>

    <h2>Words That Inspire</h2>
    <p>He once said, <q>Be the change that wish to see in the world.</q></p>
    <blockquote>
    This reminds us that real chnage begins with our own actions.
    </blockquote>

    <h3>My Reflection</h3>
    <p>I admire Mahatma Gandhi because he showed that truth,non-violence, and courage can bring about great chances. His life nspires me to be honest,kind and stand up for what is right.</p>

